    {
        "content": "<p>Usually if your goal is an implication you'll have <code>intro</code>d. A pure-tactic way to deal with this is <code>intro h; exfalso; revert h</code>.</p>",
        "id": 526169374,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1751076091
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>impl_elim</code> is too generic for <code>apply?</code> because it could match everything: for it <code>1 &lt; 2</code> could be a candidate for this with the remaining goals <code>¬?p</code>, <code>?p</code> and <code>?p : Prop</code>. This is obviously not good because it would mean we get irrelevant results for every goal. Thus, it just ignores them.</p>",
